I. Prerequisites
----------------

Go 1.18 or later.  The client has no external dependencies beyond the Go
standard library.


II. Build
---------

  cd c-golang
  go build -o cdse_client .

The resulting binary is self-contained.  Copy it anywhere on PATH if
desired.  For a quick one-off test you can also use:

  go run cdse_client.go [FLAGS] COMMAND [ARGS...]


III. Credentials
----------------

Source the env.sh file in the parent directory to export credentials for
the included development installation:

  source ../env.sh

This exports:

  CDSE_SERVER   = https://localhost:8443
  CDSE_USER_ID  = EngineAdmin
  CDSE_ORG_ID   = EngineOrg
  CDSE_ORG_KEY  = 187465950C5F9018D04F91E976CAC1D7FA19CBA5FE26D94038630B18BCBAAAB6
  CDSE_STORAGE  = EngineStorage

All examples below assume these variables are exported.  The equivalent
flags are shown in Section V for reference.

Never pass the org key on the command line in production — it appears in
shell history and process listings.  Prefer the CDSE_ORG_KEY environment
variable or interactive mode.


IV. Quick start
---------------

  # Source the development credentials
  source ../env.sh

  # Build
  go build -o cdse_client .

  # Verify the engine is reachable
  ./cdse_client -insecure info

  # Store a file as an encrypted secret
  echo "top secret payload" > /tmp/payload.txt
  ./cdse_client -insecure store-secret demo-secret /tmp/payload.txt

  # Retrieve it to stdout
  ./cdse_client -insecure get-secret demo-secret

  # Clean up
  ./cdse_client -insecure delete-secret demo-secret

For HTTP (BYPASSTLSAUTHINHTTP build) replace -insecure with
-server http://localhost:8080.


V. Command reference
--------------------

Usage:
  cdse_client [FLAGS] COMMAND [ARGS...]

Flags:

  -server  <URL|host:port>   CaumeDSE server.  Default: $CDSE_SERVER or
                             localhost:8443.  If no scheme is given, https://
                             is prepended automatically.
  -userId  <id>              userId credential.  Default: $CDSE_USER_ID.
  -orgId   <id>              orgId credential.   Default: $CDSE_ORG_ID.
  -orgKey  <key>             orgKey (encryption key).  Default: $CDSE_ORG_KEY.
                             Prefer the environment variable or interactive
                             mode to avoid shell-history exposure.
  -storage <name>            Storage bucket name.  Default: $CDSE_STORAGE or
                             EngineStorage.
  -ca-cert <path>            Path to a PEM CA certificate for TLS verification.
                             Example: -ca-cert /opt/cdse/ca.pem
  -insecure                  Disable TLS certificate verification.
                             Development/local testing only.
  -i                         Interactive mode: prompt for any missing
                             credentials, then enter a command REPL.

Commands:

  info
      Show userId, orgId, role, and storage information for the
      authenticated user.

  list-secrets
      List the names of all encrypted raw-file secrets in the storage.

  store-secret NAME FILE [INFO]
      Upload FILE and store it as an AES-256-GCM encrypted secret named NAME.
      INFO is optional free-text metadata attached to the document.

  get-secret NAME [OUTFILE]
      Retrieve and decrypt the secret named NAME.  If OUTFILE is given, the
      decrypted content is written there (mode 0600); otherwise it is written
      to stdout.

  delete-secret NAME
      Permanently delete the secret named NAME.

  db-list
      List the names of all encrypted CSV database documents.

  db-create NAME col1,col2,...
      Create a new encrypted CSV database named NAME.  Columns are given as a
      comma-separated list with no spaces.

  db-insert NAME col=val ...
      Append one row to database NAME.  Each column value is a col=val pair.
      Columns not specified remain empty.

  db-query NAME [ROW]
      Print all rows of database NAME as CSV, or print only row ROW (1-based)
      if specified.

  db-update NAME ROW col=val ...
      Update one or more columns in row ROW of database NAME.

  db-delete-row NAME ROW
      Delete row ROW from database NAME.  Rows after the deleted one are
      renumbered.

  db-delete NAME
      Delete the entire CSV database document NAME.

  audit-log
      Retrieve and print the engine's transaction audit log as CSV.

  help
      Print the command reference.


VI. Secrets — full walkthrough
--------------------------------

Prepare a test secret file:

  echo "AES-256 master key material" > /tmp/master.key

Store the secret with optional metadata:

  ./cdse_client -insecure \
      store-secret master-key /tmp/master.key "AES-256 key for prod DB"

Expected output:
  <html>...<b>200 OK - Document resource created...</b>...

List all stored secrets:

  ./cdse_client -insecure list-secrets

Retrieve the secret to a file:

  ./cdse_client -insecure get-secret master-key /tmp/master-retrieved.key

Expected output:
  Secret 'master-key' saved to /tmp/master-retrieved.key (N bytes)

Verify the round-trip:

  diff /tmp/master.key /tmp/master-retrieved.key

Retrieve to stdout:

  ./cdse_client -insecure get-secret master-key

Expected output:
  AES-256 master key material

Delete the secret:

  ./cdse_client -insecure delete-secret master-key

Expected output:
  <html>...<b>200 OK - Document resource deleted...</b>...


VII. Encrypted CSV database — full walkthrough
-----------------------------------------------

Create the database:

  ./cdse_client -insecure db-create contacts id,name,email,phone

Insert rows:

  ./cdse_client -insecure \
      db-insert contacts id=1 name=Alice email=alice@example.com phone=555-0100

  ./cdse_client -insecure \
      db-insert contacts id=2 name=Bob email=bob@example.com phone=555-0200

  ./cdse_client -insecure \
      db-insert contacts id=3 name=Carol email=carol@example.com phone=555-0300

Expected output for each insert:
  Inserted row N
  <html>...<b>200 OK...</b>...

Query all rows:

  ./cdse_client -insecure db-query contacts

Expected output (CSV):
  id,name,email,phone
  1,Alice,alice@example.com,555-0100
  2,Bob,bob@example.com,555-0200
  3,Carol,carol@example.com,555-0300

Query row 2 specifically:

  ./cdse_client -insecure db-query contacts 2

Expected output:
  id,name,email,phone
  2,Bob,bob@example.com,555-0200

Update row 1:

  ./cdse_client -insecure db-update contacts 1 email=alice@newdomain.com

Verify:

  ./cdse_client -insecure db-query contacts 1

Delete row 3:

  ./cdse_client -insecure db-delete-row contacts 3

Delete the entire database:

  ./cdse_client -insecure db-delete contacts

Confirm:

  ./cdse_client -insecure db-list


VIII. Interactive mode
----------------------

Start interactive mode; if the org key is not already set it is prompted
without echo:

  ./cdse_client -insecure -i

Or supply some credentials as flags and let the remaining ones be prompted:

  ./cdse_client -insecure -i -userId EngineAdmin -orgId EngineOrg

The connection details are shown once after login:

  Connected to localhost:8443  org=EngineOrg  user=EngineAdmin  storage=EngineStorage

At the cdse> prompt, type commands without credentials:

  cdse> info
  cdse> store-secret mykey /tmp/key.bin
  cdse> list-secrets
  cdse> get-secret mykey /tmp/out.bin
  cdse> delete-secret mykey
  cdse> db-create vault id,secret,label
  cdse> db-insert vault id=1 secret=abc123 label=dev
  cdse> db-query vault
  cdse> db-update vault 1 label=production
  cdse> db-delete-row vault 1
  cdse> db-delete vault
  cdse> audit-log
  cdse> help
  cdse> exit

Press Ctrl-D or type exit/quit to leave.


IX. Environment variable reference
------------------------------------

  CDSE_SERVER    Base URL or host:port of the CDSE instance.
                 Default: localhost:8443
                 Example: https://myserver:8443
                          http://localhost:8080  (BYPASSTLSAUTHINHTTP build)

  CDSE_USER_ID   userId credential.
                 Example: EngineAdmin

  CDSE_ORG_ID    orgId credential.
                 Example: EngineOrg

  CDSE_ORG_KEY   Organisation encryption key.  No default — must be set.
                 Example: 187465950C5F9018D04F91E976CAC1D7FA19CBA5FE26D94038630B18BCBAAAB6
                 (development installation key; see ../env.sh)

  CDSE_STORAGE   Storage bucket name.
                 Default: EngineStorage

Command-line flags override environment variables.


X. TLS options
--------------

Verify the server using the included development CA certificate:

  ./cdse_client -ca-cert /opt/cdse/ca.pem info

Disable verification (development only):

  ./cdse_client -insecure info

Use HTTP (BYPASSTLSAUTHINHTTP build, no TLS):

  ./cdse_client -server http://localhost:8080 info

Never use -insecure or the HTTP port in production.


XI. Exit codes
--------------

  0   Success.
  1   Usage error, credential error, or API error.
